\begin_layout Subsection
Convert Dia to XML
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This script converts the Dia file into the XML standard file format
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

./bin/dia_2_xml.sh -h 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

usage:
 dia_2_xml.sh -i inputfile [-a] [-c] [-h] [-k] [-v]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -a auto          generate historization fields and tables in output file
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -c check         validate generated file
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -h help          print this help text
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -i inputfile     name of input file
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -k keep          keep tempfiles,
 dop not delete at end
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -o outputfile    name of output file,
 default:
 inputfile with dia replaced by xml
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -v verbose       list all steps of execution
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The option -a (auto) adds valid-from and valid-to fields to all tables in the dim-schema and creates a copy all tables in the dim-schema into the hist schema.
 The -c (check) option checks a bunch of rules for the generated tables.
 The -h (help) option displays the help text.
 The -i inputfile gives the name of the dia diagram file to convert to the standard xml format.
 The -k (keep) options prevents the removal of the temp files at the end of the script.
 The -o outputfile option accepts an alternative name of the output file,
 default ist the same as inputfile with extension dia replaced by xml.
 The -v (verbose) options shows all called xslt and awk helper scripts with their arguments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Convert XML to SQL
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This script converts the XML standard format into SQL format for PostgreSQL
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

./bin/xml_2_db.sh -h 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

usage:
 xml_2_db.sh -i inputfile [-r reffiles] [-d database] [-u user] [-o outputfile] [-p projectfile] [-c] [-e] [-h] [-k] [-r] [-v] [-y]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -c check         check the xml file before generating sql code
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -d database      database,
 default is project name
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -e execute       execute generated sql script
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -h help          print this help text
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -i inputfile     filename to process
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -k keep          keep,
 do not delete temp files
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -o outputfile    output filename,
 default is input file name with xml replaced by sql
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -p projectfile   configuration file for historization,
 default is xml/project.xml
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -r reffiles      referencefiles:
 oldfile,newfile
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -u user          dabase user,
 default is ${USER}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -v verbose       show all execution steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -y yes           answer yes to all questions 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The -c (check) option checks a bunch of rules before trying to create sql code.
 The -d (database) option takes the name of the PostgrSQL database,
 default is the name of the project.
 The -e (execute) option executes the generated SQL script in the PostgrSQL database.
 The -h (help) option displays the help text.
 The -i inputfile gives the name of the dia diagram file to convert to the standard xml format.
 The -k (keep) options prevents the removal of the temp files at the end of the script.
 The -o outputfile option accepts an alternative name of the output file,
 default ist the same as inputfile with extension dia replaced by xml.
 The -p projectfile gives the name of the project file,
 default is xml/project.xml.
 The -r (reffiles) is needed,
 when the input file contains a diff between old and new version.
 The both files names oldfile and new file contain the complete old and new models in XML format.
 The -u (user) option gives an alternativ user for the PostgrSQL database,
 default is the Linux user name.
 The -v (verbose) options shows all called xslt and awk helper scripts with their arguments.
 The -y (yes) option is used in conjuction with the -e (execute) option and forces the execution of the SQL script without asking for confirmation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Compare two model versions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This script takes two versions of a model in XML format and creates a delta between them in XML format.
 This delta file can then be converted to SQL format to migrate the old version of the model to the new version.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

./bin/xml_2_diff.sh -h 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

usage:
 xml_2_diff.sh -i oldinputfile,newinputfile [-o outputfile] [-c] [-v]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -c check             check syntax of output file
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -h help              print this help message
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -i oldfile,newfile   names of input files,
 old file name and new file name separated with ,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -o outfile           name of output file,
 default is project_old_new.xml
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -p projectfile       configuration file for historization,
 default is xml/project.xml
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -v verbose           show all steps of execution 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The -c (check) option checks a bunch of rules for the generated diff file.
 The -h (help) option displays the help text.
 The -i oldfile,newfile option supplied the names of the old and the new model file.
 The optional -o outfile option suppiled a name for the generated diff file,
 the default name is build from the input files:
 name_v01.xml and name_v02.xml results in name_v01_v02.xml.
 The -p projectfile gives the name of the project file,
 default is xml/project.xml.
 The -v (verbose) options shows all called xslt and awk helper scripts with their arguments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Create Test Data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This script generates a SQl script with insert statements for all tables to load some test data into the tables.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

./bin/xml_2_dat.sh -h 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

usage:
 xml_2_dat.sh -i inputfile [-d database] [-u user] [-o outputfile] [-l lines] [-p projectfile] [-c] [-D] {-e|-g} [-h] [-k] [-r] [-v] [-y]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -c check         check the xml file before generating sql code
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -d database      database,
 default is projectname
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -D delete        delete all existing rows with truncate table
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -e execute       execute generated sql script
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -g generate      generate sql scripts with insert statements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -h help          print this help text
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -i inputfile     filename to process
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -k keep          keep,
 do not delete temp files
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -l lines         lines to insert,
 default is 1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -o outputfile    output filename,
 default is input file name with xml replaced by sql or dat.sql
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -p projectfile   configuration file for historization,
 default is xml/project.xml
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -u user          dabase user,
 default is ${USER}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -v verbose       show all execution steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

    -y yes           answer yes to all questions 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The -c (check) option checks a bunch of rules before generating the SQL script.
 The -d (database) option takes the name of the PostgrSQL database,
 default is the name of the project.
 The -D (delete) option writes truncate table statements at the top of the SQL script and deletes all existing data.
 The -e (execute) option executes the generated SQL script in the PostgrSQL database.
 The -g (generate) option only generates the SQL script.
 The -h (help) option displays the help text.
 The -i inputfile gives the name of the xml file with the model info.
 The -k (keep) options prevents the removal of the temp files at the end of the script.
 The -l lines option creates the supplied number of lines for dim and const tables and lines^n lines for the fact tables that reference n dim tables.
 The -o outputfile option accepts an alternative name of the output file,
 default ist the same as inputfile with extension dia replaced by xml.
 The -p projectfile gives the name of the project file,
 default is xml/project.xml.
 The -u (user) option gives an alternativ user for the PostgrSQL database,
 default is the Linux user name.
 The -v (verbose) options shows all called xslt and awk helper scripts with their arguments.
 The -y (yes) option is used in conjuction with the -e (execute) option and forces the execution of the SQL script without asking for confirmation.
\end_layout

