\begin_layout Standard
The -a (all) option shows all levels of information.
 The -c (column) option shows levels schema/table/column.
 The -f (function) option shows levels schema/functions.
 The -h (help) option displays the help text.
 The -i inputfile gives the name of the xml file with the model info.
 The -r (reference) option shows references.
 The -s (schema) option only shows level schema.
 The -t (table) option shows level schema/table.
 The -v (verbose) options shows all called xslt and awk helper scripts with their arguments.
\end_layout

